01 ACS CONFIGURATION
  GO TO =M;2 ISMF
  SWITCH TO STORAGE ADMINISTRATOR (0, 0, SA)

  EXIT AND RE-ENTER

  CHECK THE AUTOMATIC CLASS SELECTION (7)

    ACS SOURCE DATASETS:
      STORCLAS  SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.CNTL
      STORGRP   SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.CNTL


02 SMS CONFIGURATION
  D SMS
    IGD002I 11:16:52 DISPLAY SMS 426
    SCDS = SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.SCDS
    ACDS = SYS1.S0W1.ACDS
    COMMDS = SYS1.S0W1.COMMDS
    ACDS LEVEL = Z/OS V2.3
    DINTERVAL = 150
    REVERIFY = NO
    ACSDEFAULTS = NO


03 EDIT THE ACS ROUTINES
  =3.4 SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.CNTL(STORCLASS)
    ADD
      FILTLIST <instid>_HLQ          INCLUDE(<instid>.**,
                                                     <instid>*.**)

      WHEN (&HLQ = &<instid>_HLQ)
        DO
          SET &STORCLAS = 'SC<instid>'
          EXIT CODE(0)
        END

  =3.4 SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.CNTL(STORGRP)
    ADD
      WHEN (&STORCLAS = 'SC<instid>')
        DO
          SET &STORGRP = 'SG<instid>'
          EXIT CODE(0)
        END

04 RECAP OF WHAT YOU DEFINED IN STEP 3:
  STORCLASS FOR <instid>*.** <instid>*.** IS SC<instid>
  STORGROUP FOR <instid>*.** <instid>*.** IS SG<instid>

05 ISMF
  5 STORAGECLASS
    DEFINE A STORAGE CLASS
      INPUT THE CDS NAME FOUND BEFORE VIA D SMS IN THE 'CDS Name' FIELD
        CDS Name .... 'SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.SCDS'
      INPUT THE STORAGE CLASS DEFINED ABOVE
         Storage Class Name ..... SC<instid>
      PRESS ENTER
      ADD A DESCRIPTION
         Description ==> STORAGE CLASS FOR WHATEVER YOU WANT
      KEEP THE REST DEFAULT AND SAVE

  6 STORAGE GROUP
    DEFINE A STORAGE GROUP WITH THE SAME PRINCIPLE
      SET POOL AS TYPE
        CDS Name  . . . . . . 'SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.SCDS'
        Storage Group Name    SG<instid>
        Storage Group Type    POOL
    AFTER PRESSING ENTER, SET THE AUTO BACKUP INTERVAL IN DAYS
      Guaranteed Backup Frequency  . . . . . . 1

    5 (STILL FROM THE STORAGE GROUP 6 MENU): DEFINE THE VOLUMES IN SMS
      INPUT THE VOLUME (DASD) LABEL PREFIX AND FROM/TO NUMBERS

  7 AUTOMATIC CLASS SELECTION (TO TRANSLATE WHAT WE DEFINED)
    |SCDS NAME . . . . . . . 'SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.SCDS'
    |                                  (1 TO 44 CHARACTER DATA SET NAME)
    |
    |ACS SOURCE DATA SET . . 'SYS1.S0W1.DFSMS.CNTL'
    |                                  (1 TO 44 CHARACTER DATA SET NAME)
    |
    |ACS SOURCE MEMBER . . . STORCLAS  (1 TO 8 CHARACTERS)
    |
    |LISTING DATA SET  . . . OUTLIST
    |
    |                                  (1 TO 44 CHARACTER DATA SET NAME)
    |

    RUN THE SAME FOR STORGRP

    VALIDATE (3 IN THE ACS APPLICATION SELECTION)
      CHECK THAT EVERYTHING IS SUCCESSFUL
      NO WARNINGS!

08 ACTIVATE IN ISMF
  ISMF 8 (CONTROL DATASET), ACTIVATE
